               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18471025-name-664" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18471025-name-664" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18471025-name-664" type="surname" value="PICKERING"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18471025-name-664" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM PICKERING.</persName>
                  </hi> I live in Turnmill-street, Bethnal-green, and keep fowls. On the 25th of Sept., near seven o'clock, I missed a fowl—I afterwards saw the prisoner in custody—before I said anything to him, he said, "I had your fowl, it is at Rickett's house at the back of Shoreditch Church"—I went there and found it—I did not know the prisoner—to the best of my judgment the fowl which is here is mine.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18471025-name-665" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18471025-name-665" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18471025-name-665" type="surname" value="RICKETTS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18471025-name-665" type="given" value="EDWIN"></interp>EDWIN RICKETTS.</persName>
                  </hi> I am a wire-work cage-maker, and keep a bird shop—this fowl was brought to my shop on the 25th, between six and seven in the evening—I cannot say who by—I am not certain it was not the prisoner—I put it outside the door for sale.</p>
